# Files excluded from CLI-based Vercel deploys.
#
# Why this exists: `npx vercel --prod` tarballs the local project and
# uploads it to Vercel's build system. Without this file, local dev
# artifacts (including `.env.production`) get shipped to the build
# tarball. Vercel's build UI then warns "Detected .env file" because
# it sees two sources of env vars — the uploaded file AND the Vercel
# env dashboard. The dashboard is the source of truth; this file keeps
# the tarball lean.

# Env files — Vercel's env var dashboard is the single source of truth.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Local dev output that shouldn't travel to the build
.next
node_modules
.vercel

# Project ephemera
tmp/
.DS_Store
*.log

# Test / gauntlet output (was accidentally staged before)
scripts/*.log
